#. <section class="sutta" id="an8.57"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.57:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.57:0.2"
msgid "6. Gotamīvagga"
msgstr "6. Gotamī"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 57. Paṭhamaāhuneyyasutta → paṭhamaāhuneyyabhikkhusuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.57:0.3"
msgid "57. Paṭhamaāhuneyyasutta"
msgstr "57. Worthy of Offerings to the Gods (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.291"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an8.57:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo "
"dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a mendicant with eight factors is worthy of offerings dedicated "
"to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a teacher’s offering, worthy "
"of veneration with joined palms, and is a supreme field of merit for the "
"world."

msgctxt "an8.57:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi aṭṭhahi?"
msgstr "What eight?"

msgctxt "an8.57:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, and has "
"appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing danger in the "
"slightest flaw, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an8.57:1.4"
msgid "bahussuto hoti … pe … diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;"
msgstr ""
"They’re learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These "
"teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the "
"end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s "
"totally full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering "
"them, reciting them, mentally scrutinizing them, and understanding them with "
"right view."

msgctxt "an8.57:1.5"
msgid "kalyāṇamitto hoti kalyāṇasahāyo kalyāṇasampavaṅko;"
msgstr "They have good friends, companions, and associates."

msgctxt "an8.57:1.6"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, sammādassanena samannāgato;"
msgstr "They have right view, possessing right perspective."

msgctxt "an8.57:1.7"
msgid ""
"catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī "
"hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī;"
msgstr ""
"They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that "
"belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty."

msgctxt "an8.57:1.8"
msgid ""
"anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo …"
" pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati;"
msgstr "They recollect many kinds of past lives, with features and details."

msgctxt "an8.57:1.9"
msgid ""
"dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena … pe … yathākammūpage satte "
"pajānāti;"
msgstr ""
"With clairvoyance that is purified and surpasses the human, they see how "
"sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds."

msgctxt "an8.57:1.10"
msgid "āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this "
"very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to "
"the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an8.57:1.11"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … "
"pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant with these eight factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the "
"gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a teacher’s offering, worthy of "
"veneration with joined palms, and is a supreme field of merit for the world.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.57:1.12"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
